---
source: crates/aozora-cli/tests/snapshot_cli.rs
expression: "run(&[\"--help\"])"
---
Aozora Bunko notation parser CLI

Usage: aozora <COMMAND>

Commands:
  check    Run the lexer over a file and report diagnostics
  fmt      Round-trip parse ∘ serialize and emit the canonical form
  render   Render Aozora notation to HTML on stdout
  kinds    Tabulate every `NodeKind` / `PairKind` / `Severity` / `DiagnosticSource` / `Sentinel` /
           `InternalCheckCode` variant with its wire tag
  schema   Pretty-print the JSON Schema for one of the four wire envelopes
  explain  Print short prose for a `NodeKind` camelCase tag
  pandoc   Project the parsed document to a Pandoc AST. Without `--format`, prints Pandoc JSON to
           stdout (consumable by `pandoc -f json -t <FORMAT>`); with `--format`, spawns pandoc and
           pipes the JSON through it
  help     Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)

Options:
  -h, --help     Print help
  -V, --version  Print version
